               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184306120237"></xptr>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430612-name-1682" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430612-name-1682" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430612-name-1682" type="surname" value="HAMERTON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430612-name-1682" type="given" value="PATRICK"></interp>PATRICK HAMERTON</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">policeman.</hi>) I was on duty at Greenwich-fair, on the night of the 6th of June, and saw the prisoners in company for about an hour, attempting to pick pockets—I saw Dodds put his hand into the pro<lb></lb>secutor's pocket, and take a handkerchief out—I took him with it in his hand—Brown was close to him, covering him—I searched him, and found this snuff-box in his pocket, and this other handkerchief in his hat, and Dodds had this other handkerchief in his hat—I asked Brown what he did with the box—he said he had it to put his halfpence in, but there was snuff in it at the time.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Brown's Defence.</hi> I had it given me a week before, to keep my halfpence in. I sell fruit, and used the handkerchief to keep it in. I came into the fair with Dodds to see the shows; I did not know he had taken anything.</p>
